libIRC Release Notes
====================

Included below is the latest news pertaining to libIRC releases.  As
libIRC is a library intended for developers, the usual rhetoric of
requiring news or announcements apply to the "user-visible" changes
basically means most all changes that affect the public API of libIRC
should be listed here prior to a release.

----------------------------------------------------------------------
--- 2007-09-XX  Release 0.2.0                                      ---
----------------------------------------------------------------------

* fixed crash on channel departure - MasterMind (mm_202), Jeff Myers
* enhancements for plugins - Jeff Myers


----------------------------------------------------------------------
--- 2004-08-08  Release 0.1.0                                      ---
----------------------------------------------------------------------

 * convert API to C++ - Jeff Myers

preliminary open source release.


--- 
NEWS items should be formated to column 70 (M-q in emacs), no tabs
